Removed the half done class CopySource and CopySourceWithMultipleSourceLocation.java

ReplicationConfiguration : overall config for a dataset replication
- ReplicationCopyMode: Push/Pull
- ReplicationMetaData : meta data
- SourceEndPoint : define the original source
- ReplicaEndPoint : a list of replication end points
- DataFlowTopology : the data flow topology

Interface DataFlowRoutesPicker : if topology is not defined using literal, use this interface to pick the preferred route from default routes
- class DataFlowRoutesPickerBySourceCluster : pick route based on the original source location

Interface ReplicationEndPoint : describe the replication dataset information,
- abstract class: AbstractReplicationEndPoint
- actual class: SourceEndPoint/ReplicaEndPoint

Interface ReplicationLocation : describe the location information of the dataset, for dataset on hadoopFs, describe cluster name, colo name, root path etc.
- class HdfsReplicationLocation

@pcadabam can you help review? Right now the biggest concern that I have is that we cannot change the name of the source class. This will break any jobs that use that source already.

At a high level, I see two avenues:
- Keep the name with the new extended functionality (the name will be misleading)
- Add a new class DatePartitionedAvroFileSource and have DatePartitionedDailyAvroSource be a specialization. 

I haven't looked deeply in the code but I am leaning toward the second option.

@lbendig I agree with @chavdar that we should not rename the source class `DatePartitionedDailyAvroSource`. I would suggest the following,
- Create a new class called `DatePartitionedAvroFileSource` with all the changes you have.
- Make the current class `DatePartitionedDailyAvroSource` extend `DatePartitionedAvroFileSource`.
- In `DatePartitionedDailyAvroSource` override the `init(state)` , modify the `state` to set `date.partitioned.source.partition.pattern=yyyy/MM/dd` and then call `super.init(state)`. The rest should work automatically. If people choose to use the class `DatePartitionedDailyAvroSource` they do not need to set the pattern.
